column4: Skype loses Belgian court appeal after fails to comply with call data order
column5: BRUSSELS Microsoft's online communication service Skype lost an appeal in Belgium after it failed to comply with a court request to share data from messages and calls.

column4: Skype loses Belgian court appeal after fails to comply with call data order
column5: BRUSSELS  Nov 15 Microsoft's online communication service Skype lost an appeal in Belgium after it failed to comply with a court request to share data from messages and calls.

column4: UPDATE 1-Firefox opts for Google as default search in U.S.  surprising Yahoo
column5: SAN FRANCISCO  Nov 14 Alphabet Inc's Google reclaimed on Tuesday its spot as the default search engine on Mozilla Corp's Firefox Internet browser in the United States and other regions as the browser maker stunned Verizon Communication Inc's Yahoo by canceling their deal.

column4: Apple leads way in tracing cobalt from Congo  Microsoft lags: Amnesty
column5: LONDON Apple is leading the way in tracing cobalt used in its electronics to ensure the metal has not been mined by children in Democratic Republic of Congo while Microsoft is lagging  Amnesty International said.

column4: Jurvetson quits VC firm DFJ  on leave from Tesla amid harassment probe
column5: (This version of the November 13th story corrects paragraph 3 to remove incorrect reference to SpaceX being owned by Tesla)

column4: CORRECTED-UPDATE 1-VC firm DFJ probes sexual harassment charges against founding partner
column5: Oct 24 Venture capital firm Draper Fisher Jurvetson (DFJ)  which has invested in SpaceX  said it is independently probing sexual harassment allegations against its founding partner Steve Jurvetson.

column4: CORRECTED-UPDATE 1-Jurvetson quits VC firm DFJ  on leave from Tesla amid harassment probe
column5: Nov 13 Steve Jurvetson on Monday resigned from venture capital firm Draper Fisher Jurvetson (DFJ) and took a leave of absence from the boards of Tesla Inc and SpaceX amid an internal probe into sexual harassment allegations made against him.

column4: Tesla says it will fight lawsuit claiming racial discrimination
column5: Tesla Inc  said on Wednesday it would fight a class-action lawsuit filed against it earlier this week claiming the electric automaker's California production plant was a "hotbed for racist behavior."

column4: Qualcomm-NXP ruling may be in 2018: EU competition commissioner
column5: BEIJING A ruling on Qualcomm Inc's proposed $38 billion acquisition of NXP Semiconductors NV may come in 2018  European Commissioner for Competition Margrethe Vestager said on Wednesday.
